Summary:
=========
Papers downloaded: 9
Datasets documented: 3 (1 with samples downloaded)
Repositories cloned: 2

Research Topic: LLMs are bad at keeping obvious secrets
Hypothesis: LLMs reveal/foreshadow information because planning and prose generation are entangled

Key Findings:
=============
1. No existing work directly studies "secret-keeping" in story generation
2. Plan-and-write approaches (hierarchical generation) improve coherence but may leak plan info
3. Suspense/uncertainty metrics from Wilmot & Keller (2020) can be adapted
4. WritingPrompts is the primary dataset for story generation research
5. doc-storygen-v2 provides a ready-to-use plan-and-write framework

